    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The ground in a 20-foot radius centered on a point within range twists and sprouts hard spikes and thorns. The area becomes &amp;Reference[rule=difficultterrain]{difficult terrain} for the duration. When a creature moves into or within the area, it takes [[/damage 2d4 type=piercing]] damage for every 5 feet it travels.</p><p>The transformation of the ground is camouflaged to look natural. Any creature that can't see the area at the time the spell is cast must make a Wisdom (&amp;Reference[skill=Perception]) check against your spell save DC to recognize the terrain as hazardous before entering it.</p></div>",
